From 98a0804d03b0f27fe04ee1f79531cccf4c83c847 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sami Jaghouar <sami.jaghouar@hotmail.fr>
Date: Tue, 24 Feb 2026 23:12:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] chore: move tool_call_parser resolution from config
 validation to server startup

The auto-detection ran at config time via a model_validator, but the model
name may not be final yet (e.g. RLConfig propagates it later), requiring a
hacky reset+re-resolve in auto_setup_model(). Moving the lookup to
server() ensures we always resolve against the final model name.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
